Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of @water{} and @salt{}(to taste) to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Zest and quarter @lemon{1%unit}. Cut @Roma Tomato{2%unit} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Arrange tomato wedges on prepared sheet, skin sides down. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tsp} and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tsp} (save the rest for step 4). Roast on top rack until softened and beginning to release their juices, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once tomatoes have roasted ~{10%minutes}, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to pot of boiling water. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain. Set spaghetti aside in #strainer{}; keep pot handy for use in step 5.

Pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and remaining @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tbsp}. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in pot used for spaghetti over medium-low heat. Whisk in lemon zest, @Cream Cheese{2%tbsp}, and ⅓ cup reserved pasta cooking water (¾ cup for 4) until smooth. Stir in spaghetti, @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tbsp}, half the @Parmesan Cheese{¼%cup} (you'll use the rest later), and juice from half the lemon (whole lemon for 4).

> TIP: If pasta seems dry, add more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until coated in a creamy sauce.

Stir in chicken and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pick @Basil{½%oz} leaves from stems; discard stems and roughly chop or tear leaves. Divide spaghetti between #bowls{} and top with tomato wedges. Garnish with basil leaves and remaining Parmesan and serve.